17 that one of the two initial members appointed by each governing body shall serve for two
18 years. The fourteen members so appointed shall appoint the fifteenth member, who shall
19 be a resident of Clay, Harris, Marion, Quitman, Randolph, Stewart, Webster, and The
20 Unified Government of Cusseta-Chattahoochee counties for a term of four years. Members
21 of the Authority shall serve the term specified and until their successors are appointed and
22 qualified; provided however, that any member of the Authority may be removed at any
23 time by the governing Authority which appointed such member, with or without cause.
24 Any member of the Authority may be selected and appointed to succeed himself or herself.
25 Any vacancy on the Authority shall be filled in the same manner as was the original
26 appointment of the member whose term of membership resulted in such vacancy, and the
27 person so selected and appointed shall serve for the remainder of the expired term. The
28 members of the Authority shall be reimbursed out of the funds of the Authority for all
29 actual expenses incurred in the performance of their duties. The Authority shall make rules
30 and regulations for its own government. The Authority shall have perpetual existence."
31 SECTION 2.
32 Said Act is further amended by revising Section 13 as follows:
33 "SECTION 13.
34 Credit not pledged.
35 Revenue Bonds issued under the provisions of this Act shall not be deemed to constitute
36 a debt of Clay, Harris, Marion, Quitman, Randolph, Stewart, Webster, and The Unified
37 Government of Cusseta-Chattahoochee counties nor pledge of faith and credit of any of
38 said counties; but such bonds shall be payable solely from the funds provided in this Act,
39 and the issuance of such revenue bonds shall not directly, indirectly, or contingently
40 obligate said counties to levy or pledge any form of taxation whatever therefore or to make
